{
  "text": "Lipid Solubility. The octanol-water-based partitioning between the liver slice and medium for tolbutamide was estimated in [CITATION_1] to be P hm ϭ 0.858. This estimation was based on an algorithm for predicting partition coefficients from octanol-water partition coefficient data [CITATION_2] . The same partitioning is assumed between the hepatocytes and medium. Moreover, the sensitivity of the time course of the concentration in the medium to this parameter is low. Because neither the medium nor collagen contained a fat fraction, the collagen-medium partition coefficient P cm ϭ 1 was assumed. This was consistent with the experiments regarding the molecular diffusion of tolbutamide.",
